{"id":442595,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Icchokas_Meras","text":"Icchokas Meras (8 October 1934 \u2013 13 March 2014) was a Lithuanian-Israeli writer and screenwriter. On 6 December 2010, he was awarded the Lithuanian National Prize. He was born in Kelm\u0117, \u0160iauliai County. He was Jewish and survived the Holocaust.\nMeras died in Tel Aviv, Israel. He was 79 years old.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"Lithuanians","surface_form":"Lithuanian","offset":54},{"uri":"Israel","surface_form":"Israel","offset":65},{"uri":"Writer","surface_form":"writer","offset":73},{"uri":"Screenwriter","surface_form":"screenwriter","offset":84},{"uri":"Lithuanian_National_Prize","surface_form":"Lithuanian National Prize","offset":137},{"uri":"Kelm%C4%97","surface_form":"Kelm\u0117","offset":179},{"uri":"%C5%A0iauliai_County","surface_form":"\u0160iauliai County","offset":186},{"uri":"Jewish","surface_form":"Jewish","offset":210},{"uri":"Holocaust","surface_form":"Holocaust","offset":234},{"uri":"Tel_Aviv","surface_form":"Tel Aviv","offset":259},{"uri":"Israel","surface_form":"Israel","offset":269}]}